A8X.F.summary: Fiskars Oyj Abp manufactures and markets consumer products in Europe, the Americas, and the Asia Pacific. The company operates through three segments: Living, Functional, and Other. It offers a range of products for tabletop, giftware, and interior dÃ©cor under the Waterford, Wedgwood, Royal Albert, Royal Doulto, Iittala, Royal Copenhagen, RÃ¶rstrand, and Arabia brands. The company also provides home, gardening, and outdoor products under the Fiskars, Gerber, and Gilmour brands. In addition, it develops, manages, and rents real estate properties; and sells timber. Fiskars Oyj Abp was founded in 1649 and is headquartered in Helsinki, Finland.
